{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Fund pension supplement for WW2 veterans to cover all living costs ",
        "additional_details": "Poverty is rife among Britain's oldest citizens, including WW2 veterans, and many have to choose between eating or heating their homes due to ever increasing Utility bills, local Council taxes, and a low State pension.\r\n\r\nThe basic state pension is only around \u00a37,000 a year. We demand this is increased substantially, with a supplement to cover all living costs, such as council tax, rent and utilities.\r\n\r\nWithout this Generation\u2019s past efforts and sacrifices during WW2, none of us would be here today.\r\n",
        "background": "The Government should provide \u201cCradle to Grave\u201d care for WW2 veterans, by ensuring that Income Tax and National Insurance contributions paid into the system through a working life, come back in the form of a decent State pension on reaching retirement age.  ",
